casebody.data:
WILLIAM F. HEINS, Plaintiff and Appellant, v. CHARLES A. PEINE, Defendant and Respondent.

Before Monell, Sedgwick, and Van Vorst, JJ.

Decided February 1, 1873. C. Bainbridge Smith, for appellant. John J. Townsend, for respondent. Appeal from a judgment in favor of defendant for a return of personal property. Judgment affirmed.

Opinion by Sedgwick, J. Monell and Van Vorst, JJ., concurred.
